Text.string: Oh, hey! I almost forgot about this Clapslist mission. I was supposed to find someone to help debug this game called Destroyer of Worlds! I'm detecting a long-lost copy of the game on Nekrotafeyo. Find it and shove it in your ECHO device! It'll probably be fine.
Thank you for your purchase!
Thank you for trying one of our many exciting missions from Destroyer of Worlds! But there is more content to explore! Now, head to the next portal hotspot to continue the game!
Ooh, boy. This game is really in bad shape...||—Oh, hey! Ready for another exciting adventure? Let's chat!
Uh oh! It looks like a new portal is opening! But Lana's powers are dwindling! You'll have to fetch some Lek'tosh crystals to help her regain her powers!
Please, hero... I need those crystals!
Whoops. That's not supposed to happen. And the objective is bugging out, too... Wow, that is a lot of crystals to fetch. Oh well! Better get to it!

Oh, hey! We've got a solution for our little bug problem! Would you like to purchase our BRAND NEW “Ascendant Energy” pack of ninety Lek'tosh crystals to speed up your progress? So convenient! Shoot your selection now!
Thank you for your purchase!
Yes, hero! That's it! Now bring me those Lek'tosh crystals so I might regain my strength!
I can feel the energy surging through me! Now help me close this Ry'ek portal!
Ah, these lands are cleansed of Rak'nagob's scourge... for now!

Thank you for playing another thrilling Destroyer of Worlds mission! But Rak'nagob is still trying to invade our world! It's time for one last showdown, and one more microtransaction opportunity! Find the last portal hotspot!

Thank you for your help in testing our private early access augmented-reality game: Destroyer of Worlds! I'm Mickey Tricks, the Marketing Exploitation Director. In our game, the great evil known as Rak'nagob is trying to infiltrate our world through these Ry'ek Portal things—anyway, blah blah blah, story story story. Find the first portal hotspot to start playing!
Okay, just one more borked-ass mission to get through here.||—Hey, hero! Let me know when you're ready for the ultimate battle with Rak'nagob!
This is it! The big one! Despite your best efforts, Rak'nagob is trying to break through this portal into our world and blah, blah, blah. Stop him with bullets!
STATE TRANSITION: Dead.

Looks like it's taking a while to penetrate Rak'nagob's interdimensional hide, huh? But it's okay! We JUST added an Armor Shatter perk to the in-game store which will break his natural armor—because we're just super helpful like that! Care to buy it? Of course you do!
Thank you for your purchase!
You've done it! Rak'nagob is destroyed, and we've got a few more microtransaction bucks in our pocket! Now, please speak to me to receive your game tester stipend.

Okay, real quick, more story stuff: this is the sorceress, Lana Sh'ani. She can close the portals with her powerful magicks-with-a-k, but you'll need to escort her to ensure her safety. Now go shoot some stuff!

Thank you for playing! Destroyer of Worlds will be available for public early access any day now! And with all the money we've made from these super-convenient microtransactions, we will DEFINITELY finish the game. Promise!
Looks like you can talk to that guy to get started!
Hey there, hero! Ready to play Destroyer of Worlds?

Okay, real quick, more story stuff: this is the sorceress, Lana Sh'ani. She can close the portals with her powerful magicks-with-a-k, but you'll need to escort her to ensure her safety—whoops! There she goes! Better get started!
Oh no! Those big scary Drak'nars are trying to kill Lana! Help her!
Those enemies are just placeholders, by the way. They'll be much bigger and scarier eventually. But isn't this game already SO GREAT?!
Hey, listen! I'm under attack.
Protect me!
They're attacking!
Stop them, hero!

Now here's the REALLY exciting part! For a minor fee, you can purchase a Wingshoe walking speed upgrade for Lana! Aren't you just super stoked to buy something from the in-game store? Shoot your selection now!
Whoops! Looks like the “No” button doesn't work. I'll put in a bug report for that. But it's okay, you totally want that upgrade, right?
That's one portal closed! Great work, hero!
Uh oh... looks like Lana's slowing down again. But don't worry! We're here to help! And you can buy another Wingshoe movement speed upgrade right now! How convenient, right?!
Another wicked Ry'ek portal! We must close it now, hero!
Thank you for your help closing this portal!
Looks like that Wingshoe upgrade wears off pretty quick! Bummer. But don't worry! You can always buy another one! Like right now!
Thank you for your purchase!
Whoops! Looks like a little pathing bug there. Don't worry, I'm sure it'll fix itself here in a second.
There we go. Onward, to adventure!
I'm fading from existence! Assist me!
They got me! I require aid!
Save me, hero! I'm dying!
I'm mightily wounded! I need help!
Come, hero! Our task is nigh! We must close this Ry'ek portal!
The world is a bit safer now—thanks to you, hero!

Wow. You... REALLY didn't want to buy that thing, huh? I just don't understand that at all. What? Did you want some kind of reward? No, no, no. I think having the time to pick up all one-hundred crystals is a reward in and of itself.
Don't worry about the enemy model. That's a placeholder. We'll get something totally rad in there soon! Trust me!
Now we must close this final portal! Help me, hero!
Better seal up that last portal, hero!
Please feel free to find me on social media and leave us a review letting us know how much you LOVED Destroyer of Worlds!
Oh, man... Crap, this game is barely playable.||—Oh, hey, hero! Come chat with me to get started on your adventure!
Yep. It, uh, it still doesn't work.
Like I said... the “No” button isn't working, hero.
Look, just give us your money. We'll fix the “No” button later.
Whoops, that “No” button still isn't working. Oh well, you know you want that upgrade!
Yeah, that “No” button is still busted.
The “No” button is still bugged, but it's okay, right? Don't you want that Wingshoe upgrade?!
Wuh oh. The “No” still isn't working. Better pick up that Wingshoe upgrade!
Yep... still not working.
Just buy the upgrade, so we can move on, okay?
Well, looks like ALL our “No” buttons are broken. But hey! This is a great deal on ninety whole Lek'tosh crystals!
Come on, you know you want to bypass this fetch quest. This microtransaction is here to help!
Just give us the money and buy the crystals, hero!
Thank you for your purchase!
Lucky for you, that “No” button doesn't work. I'm sure you meant to shoot “Yes,” right?
It's gonna take a LOT of bullets to cut through that interdimensional hide! Don't you want the Armor Shatter perk?
Oh, come on, we're tryin' to help you out here. Just buy the upgrade!

Wow, you did it without the upgrade? That was painful to watch. How much ammo did you burn through? That's some serious dedication to avoiding microtransactions. I really just don't understand you at all, hero.
Our fears have been realized! Rak'nagob is trying to break into our world! Help me close this foul Ry'ek portal!
